\section{Introduction}
This guide provides instructions for setting up and using the application. It is intended for developers and end-users who want to interact with the API or use the application's features.

\section{Installation}
1. Clone the repository:
   \begin{itemize}
     \item Git clone command: \texttt{git clone https://github.com/your-repository.git}
   \end{itemize}

2. Install dependencies:
   \begin{itemize}
     \item Run \texttt{npm install} in the project directory.
   \end{itemize}

\section{Configuration}
1. Create a `.env` file based on the provided `.env.example`.
2. Update the environment variables as needed.

\section{Getting Started}
1. Start the application:
   \begin{itemize}
     \item Run \texttt{npm start} to start the server.
   \end{itemize}

\section{API Endpoints}
For detailed API documentation, refer to the `api-docs.md` file or visit:
\url{http://localhost:3000/api-docs}

\section{Features}
- User authentication
- Post creation and management
- API key-based access control

\section{Troubleshooting}
1. Common Issues:
   \begin{itemize}
     \item Ensure all environment variables are correctly set.
     \item Check network connectivity to external services.
   \end{itemize}

2. Logs:
   - Application logs are stored in the `logs` directory.

\section{Contact Us}
For questions or support, email us at support@yourdomain.com.

